theorem P1_imp_P1_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    Topology.P1 A → Topology.P1 (closure A) := by
  intro hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1] at hP1
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hx_closA
  -- From `P1 A` we obtain `closure A ⊆ closure (interior A)`
  have h₁ : closure A ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
    have h := closure_mono hP1
    simpa [closure_closure] using h
  -- `interior` is monotone, so `interior A ⊆ interior (closure A)`
  have h_int_subset : interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
    apply interior_mono
    intro y hy
    have hA : y ∈ A := interior_subset hy
    exact subset_closure hA
  -- Taking closures preserves inclusion
  have h₂ : closure (interior A) ⊆ closure (interior (closure A)) :=
    closure_mono h_int_subset
  -- Combine the two inclusions to reach the goal
  have : x ∈ closure (interior A) := h₁ hx_closA
  exact h₂ this

theorem interior_subset_interior_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior A ⊆ interior (closure A) := by
  exact interior_mono subset_closure
